```
                    +----------------------------------+
                    |    Vercel — apps/web (cloud)     |
                    |  React 19 SPA (Slide Center UI)  |
                    |  Sentry runtime (DSN EU)         |
                    +----------------+-----------------+
                                     |
                  +------------------+------------------+
                  |                                     |
        Supabase (cloud)                       Tauri 2 desktop
        ─────────────────                      ─────────────────
        PostgreSQL 17 + RLS                    apps/desktop (binario unico)
        Auth (JWT app_metadata)                ├ Webview = SPA apps/web
        Storage (TUS resumable)                ├ Server Rust Axum (127.0.0.1:dynamic)
        Realtime (Postgres+Broadcast)          ├ SQLite locale + WAL
        Edge Functions Deno (26)               ├ mDNS _slidecenter._tcp.local
        Cron pg_cron (cleanup ping)            └ NSIS installer + Updater Tauri
                  |
                  +-------- Live WORKS APP (SaaS partner)
                            licensing webhook → licensing-sync Edge Fn
                            (Lemon Squeezy backend live-software11)
```

## Catena dati END-TO-END (esempio: cliente carica file → PC sala lo proietta)

1. **Speaker** (anon, no account) apre URL `https://app.../u/<upload_token>` (route `apps/web/src/features/upload-portal/`).
2. SPA chiama Supabase Storage TUS endpoint `/storage/v1/upload/resumable` con `bucketName: 'presentations'` e path `tenants/<tenant>/events/<event>/presentations/<id>/v<n>/<file>`.
3. Lato DB trigger `update_storage_used()` aggiorna quota tenant; trigger `check_storage_quota()` blocca se sopra limite.
4. SPA crea row `presentation_versions` con `status='ready'`, `sha256=<hash>`, `size_bytes=<n>`, `uploaded_via='speaker'`.
5. Trigger Realtime su `presentation_versions` → channel `event:<event_id>` riceve `INSERT` → admin/coordinator vedono nuova versione live.
6. Coordinator/admin clicca "Pubblica" → UPDATE `presentations.current_version_id` → trigger Realtime + trigger Broadcast su `room:<room_id>`.
7. **PC sala (Room Player)** browser anon su `https://app.../sala/<device_token>`:
   - Bootstrap iniziale via Edge Fn `room-player-bootstrap` → sala + manifest + topic Broadcast UUID.
   - Subscribe `supabase.channel('room:<uuid>')` su evento `presentation_changed`.
   - Hook `useFileSync` riceve evento → fetch nuova `presentation_version` → calcola path → File System Access API → download streaming + verify SHA-256 → notifica `synced`.
8. Tecnico in sala apre il file dal disco locale (PowerPoint/Keynote) — file gia' presente, zero buffering.

## Catena LAN-only (Sprint M-N — admin offline, sala offline, LAN attiva)

1. PC admin apre `apps/desktop` (Tauri 2). Setup ruolo `admin`, server Rust su `127.0.0.1:N`, mDNS publish `role=admin`.
2. PC sala apre `apps/desktop`. Setup ruolo `sala`, server Rust su `127.0.0.1:M`, mDNS publish `role=sala`.
3. SPA admin (modalita desktop): `cmd_discover_lan_pcs(role_filter='sala')` ritorna lista PC sala visibili.
4. Admin sceglie un PC sala → genera codice 6 cifre → Tauri command `pair_direct_lan({targetBaseUrl, ...})` → POST `/functions/v1/pair-direct` sul server Rust della sala con codice + `device_name` + `event_id`.
5. Sala valida codice + persiste `device.json` con `pair_token_hash` + `network_mode='lan-online'`. Risponde `{device_token: "<sha256>"}`.
6. Admin riceve `device_token`, lo registra anche sul proprio admin-locale via `registerPairedDeviceOnAdminLocal({...})` (per fan-out futuro).
7. Admin carica file via Supabase Storage cloud OR via `/storage/v1/object/...` del proprio server Rust (modalita full-LAN).
8. `lan_push.rs` su admin → POST `/events/file_added` su tutti i PC sala paired in `network_mode='lan-online'`.
9. PC sala riceve evento → SPA in long-poll su `/events/stream?since=N&event_id=<uuid>` → riceve evento immediatamente.
10. Hook `useFileSync` su sala chiama `signLanDownloadUrl({adminBaseUrl, deviceToken, storageKey})` → admin firma URL HMAC-SHA256 (scadenza 30 min) → sala scarica via `/storage-files/...` con HTTP Range.

